    "body": "Hmmm, ok, so we have two issues here. One is to make geth play nice with ~~sigint~~ SIGTERM, I think that's a reasonable request, will do it. The other issue is that geth start up with 128 blocks behind. This was meant as a way to quickly pull in 128 blocks into memory on startup, but I think there's a lot of confusion stemming form it. Maybe we should just write out the last state on shutdown instead.",
